<h1>Blake Boles</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.blakeboles.com/now/">blakeboles.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
South Lake Tahoe
CA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Author and Founder/Director of Unschool Adventures
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I help young adults challenge themselves, feel engaged, and become better self-directed learners.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Being bored as a teenager is a terrible waste of opportunity. I want to share the joy and empowerment that I felt attending summer camps and traveling internationally with as many young people as possible.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
The 4-hour-work-week dream isn't for me. <<a href="http://www.blakeboles.com/2015/10/freedom-businesses/>">http://www.blakeboles.com/2015/10/freedom-businesses/></a>
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
“The Unbearable Lightness of Being Scott Williamson” by Steve Friedman <<a href="http://www.backpacker.com/trips/washington/the-unbearable-lightness-of-being-scott-williamson/>">http://www.backpacker.com/trips/washington/the-unbearable-lightness-of-being-scott-williamson/></a>
</p>

